---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="BMI Calculator by Age (2026) – Age-Adjusted BMI Chart & Results"
  description="Calculate your BMI with age-adjusted interpretations. Check healthy weight ranges for seniors and kids."
  keywords="bmi calculator by age, bmi chart by age, bmi for elderly, age adjusted bmi, senior weight standards"
  canonicalUrl="https://calbmi.com/bmi-calculator-by-age.html"
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline>
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "WebApplication",
      "name": "CalBmi - BMI Calculator by Age",
      "url": "https://calbmi.com/bmi-calculator-by-age.html",
      "description": "Calculate Body Mass Index (BMI) with age-adjusted interpretations.",
      "applicationCategory": "HealthApplication",
      "operatingSystem": "All",
      "browserRequirements": "Requires JavaScript. Requires HTML5.",
      "offers": { "@type": "Offer", "price": "0.00", "priceCurrency": "USD" },
      "aggregateRating": {
        "@type": "AggregateRating",
        "ratingValue": "4.8",
        "ratingCount": "121",
        "bestRating": "5",
        "worstRating": "1"
      }
    }
    </script>
  </Fragment>

  <!-- Calculator Section -->
  <section id="calculator" class="calc-section" style="padding-top:2.5rem">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="bmi-page-header scroll-reveal">
        <a href="/" class="back-link">
          <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="15 18 9 12 15 6"/></svg>
          Home
        </a>
        <div class="bmi-page-title-block">
          <span class="hero-badge" style="margin:0">
            ⏳ Age Group Adjusted
          </span>
          <h1 class="bmi-page-title">BMI Calculator <span class="hero-gradient">by Age</span></h1>
        </div>
        <p class="bmi-page-sub">Analyze your Body Mass Index with age-adjusted recommendations for children, adults, and seniors.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="calc-grid">
        <!-- Input Card -->
        <div class="card calc-card scroll-reveal" style="--reveal-delay:0.05s">
          <div class="card-header">
            <h2 class="card-title">Enter Your Details</h2>
            <p class="card-subtitle">Fill in your measurements below</p>
          </div>

          <!-- Unit Toggle -->
          <div class="unit-toggle-group" role="group" aria-label="Unit system">
            <button class="unit-btn active" id="btnMetric" data-unit="metric" onclick="setUnit('metric')">Metric</button>
            <button class="unit-btn" id="btnImperial" data-unit="imperial" onclick="setUnit('imperial')">Imperial</button>
          </div>

          <form id="bmiForm" class="bmi-form" novalidate>
            <!-- Age -->
            <div class="form-group">
              <label class="form-label" for="ageInput">Age <span class="label-hint">(2 – 120 years)</span></label>
              <div class="input-wrapper">
                <svg class="input-icon" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><circle cx="12" cy="8" r="4"/><path d="M4 20c0-4 3.58-7 8-7s8 3 8 7"/></svg>
                <input class="form-input" type="number" id="ageInput" placeholder="e.g. 68" min="2" max="120" />
                <span class="input-unit">yrs</span>
              </div>
              <div class="form-error" id="ageError"></div>
            </div>

            <!-- Gender -->
            <div class="form-group">
              <label class="form-label">Gender</label>
              <div class="gender-group">
                <label class="gender-option" id="genderMaleLabel">
                  <input type="radio" name="gender" value="male" id="genderMale" checked />
                  <span class="gender-card">
                    <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><circle cx="12" cy="8" r="4"/><path d="M4 20c0-4 3.58-7 8-7s8 3 8 7"/></svg>
                    Male
                  </span>
                </label>
                <label class="gender-option" id="genderFemaleLabel">
                  <input type="radio" name="gender" value="female" id="genderFemale" />
                  <span class="gender-card">
                    <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><circle cx="12" cy="8" r="4"/><path d="M4 20c0-4 3.58-7 8-7s8 3 8 7"/><path d="M9 20h6"/></svg>
                    Female
                  </span>
                </label>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Height (Metric) -->
            <div class="form-group" id="heightMetricGroup">
              <label class="form-label" for="heightCm">Height</label>
              <div class="input-wrapper">
                <svg class="input-icon" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 2v20M4 6l3 3M4 12h4M4 18l3-3M20 6l-3 3M20 12h-4M20 18l-3-3"/></svg>
                <input class="form-input" type="number" id="heightCm" placeholder="e.g. 175" min="50" max="280" />
                <span class="input-unit">cm</span>
              </div>
              <div class="form-error" id="heightCmError"></div>
            </div>

            <!-- Height (Imperial) -->
            <div class="form-group hidden" id="heightImperialGroup">
              <label class="form-label">Height</label>
              <div class="imperial-row">
                <div class="input-wrapper">
                  <svg class="input-icon" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 2v20"/></svg>
                  <input class="form-input" type="number" id="heightFt" placeholder="5" min="1" max="9" />
                  <span class="input-unit">ft</span>
                </div>
                <div class="input-wrapper">
                  <input class="form-input" type="number" id="heightIn" placeholder="9" min="0" max="11" />
                  <span class="input-unit">in</span>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="form-error" id="heightImperialError"></div>
            </div>

            <!-- Weight (Metric) -->
            <div class="form-group" id="weightMetricGroup">
              <label class="form-label" for="weightKg">Weight</label>
              <div class="input-wrapper">
                <svg class="input-icon" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 3a3 3 0 0 1 3 3H9a3 3 0 0 1 3-3z"/><rect x="3" y="6" width="18" height="15" rx="2"/></svg>
                <input class="form-input" type="number" id="weightKg" placeholder="e.g. 70" min="2" max="600" step="0.1" />
                <span class="input-unit">kg</span>
              </div>
              <div class="form-error" id="weightKgError"></div>
            </div>

            <!-- Weight (Imperial) -->
            <div class="form-group hidden" id="weightImperialGroup">
              <label class="form-label" for="weightLbs">Weight</label>
              <div class="input-wrapper">
                <svg class="input-icon" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 3a3 3 0 0 1 3 3H9a3 3 0 0 1 3-3z"/><rect x="3" y="6" width="18" height="15" rx="2"/></svg>
                <input class="form-input" type="number" id="weightLbs" placeholder="e.g. 154" min="5" max="1300" step="0.1" />
                <span class="input-unit">lbs</span>
              </div>
              <div class="form-error" id="weightLbsError"></div>
            </div>

            <button type="submit" class="calc-btn" id="calcBtn">
              <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M9 11l3 3L22 4"/><path d="M21 12v7a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V5a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h11"/></svg>
              Calculate BMI
            </button>

            <button type="button" class="reset-btn" id="resetBtn" onclick="resetForm()">
              <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M3 12a9 9 0 1 0 9-9 9.75 9.75 0 0 0-6.74 2.74L3 8"/><path d="M3 3v5h5"/></svg>
              Reset
            </button>
          </form>
        </div>

        <!-- Result Card -->
        <div class="card result-card scroll-reveal" style="--reveal-delay:0.15s" id="resultCard">
          <div class="result-placeholder" id="resultPlaceholder">
            <div class="placeholder-icon">
              <svg width="64" height="64" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5">
                <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/>
                <path d="M12 8v4l3 3"/>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <p class="placeholder-text">Enter your details and click <strong>Calculate BMI</strong> to see your results</p>
          </div>

          <div class="result-content hidden" id="resultContent">
            <!-- Gauge -->
            <div class="gauge-container">
              <svg class="gauge-svg" viewBox="0 0 220 130" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                <defs>
                  <linearGradient id="gaugeUnderweight" x1="0%" y1="0%" x2="100%" y2="0%">
                    <stop offset="0%" stop-color="#60a5fa"/>
                    <stop offset="100%" stop-color="#3b82f6"/>
                  </linearGradient>
                  <linearGradient id="gaugeNormal" x1="0%" y1="0%" x2="100%" y2="0%">
                    <stop offset="0%" stop-color="#34d399"/>
                    <stop offset="100%" stop-color="#10b981"/>
                  </linearGradient>
                  <linearGradient id="gaugeOverweight" x1="0%" y1="0%" x2="100%" y2="0%">
                    <stop offset="0%" stop-color="#fbbf24"/>
                    <stop offset="100%" stop-color="#f59e0b"/>
                  </linearGradient>
                  <linearGradient id="gaugeObese" x1="0%" y1="0%" x2="100%" y2="0%">
                    <stop offset="0%" stop-color="#f87171"/>
                    <stop offset="100%" stop-color="#ef4444"/>
                  </linearGradient>
                  <filter id="gaugeShadow">
                    <feDropShadow dx="0" dy="2" stdDeviation="3" flood-color="rgba(0,0,0,0.2)"/>
                  </filter>
                </defs>

                <!-- Background arcs -->
                <path d="M 20 115 A 90 90 0 0 1 57.5 36.4" stroke="url(#gaugeUnderweight)" stroke-width="18" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" opacity="0.3"/>
                <path d="M 57.5 36.4 A 90 90 0 0 1 110 25" stroke="url(#gaugeNormal)" stroke-width="18" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" opacity="0.3"/>
                <path d="M 110 25 A 90 90 0 0 1 162.5 36.4" stroke="url(#gaugeOverweight)" stroke-width="18" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" opacity="0.3"/>
                <path d="M 162.5 36.4 A 90 90 0 0 1 200 115" stroke="url(#gaugeObese)" stroke-width="18" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" opacity="0.3"/>

                <!-- Active arcs -->
                <path id="arcUnderweight" d="M 20 115 A 90 90 0 0 1 57.5 36.4" stroke="url(#gaugeUnderweight)" stroke-width="18" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" opacity="0" class="arc-segment"/>
                <path id="arcNormal" d="M 57.5 36.4 A 90 90 0 0 1 110 25" stroke="url(#gaugeNormal)" stroke-width="18" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" opacity="0" class="arc-segment"/>
                <path id="arcOverweight" d="M 110 25 A 90 90 0 0 1 162.5 36.4" stroke="url(#gaugeOverweight)" stroke-width="18" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" opacity="0" class="arc-segment"/>
                <path id="arcObese" d="M 162.5 36.4 A 90 90 0 0 1 200 115" stroke="url(#gaugeObese)" stroke-width="18" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" opacity="0" class="arc-segment"/>

                <!-- Needle -->
                <g id="gaugeNeedle" transform="rotate(0, 110, 115)">
                  <line x1="110" y1="115" x2="110" y2="40" stroke="var(--foreground)" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" filter="url(#gaugeShadow)"/>
                  <circle cx="110" cy="115" r="7" fill="var(--foreground)" filter="url(#gaugeShadow)"/>
                  <circle cx="110" cy="115" r="4" fill="var(--background)"/>
                </g>

                <!-- BMI Value -->
                <text id="gaugeBmiValue" x="110" y="95" text-anchor="middle" class="gauge-value-text" font-size="22" font-weight="800" fill="var(--foreground)">–</text>
                <text x="110" y="108" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="var(--muted-foreground)" font-weight="500">BMI</text>

                <!-- Labels -->
                <text x="10" y="128" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#3b82f6" font-weight="600">Under</text>
                <text x="65" y="28" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#10b981" font-weight="600">Normal</text>
                <text x="157" y="28" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#f59e0b" font-weight="600">Over</text>
                <text x="210" y="128" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#ef4444" font-weight="600">Obese</text>
              </svg>
            </div>

            <!-- Category Badge -->
            <div class="category-badge-container">
              <div class="category-badge" id="categoryBadge">
                <span id="categoryIcon"></span>
                <span id="categoryText">–</span>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Stats Grid -->
            <div class="stats-grid">
              <div class="stat-item">
                <div class="stat-label">Your BMI</div>
                <div class="stat-value" id="statBmi">–</div>
              </div>
              <div class="stat-item">
                <div class="stat-label">Healthy Range</div>
                <div class="stat-value stat-small" id="statRange">18.5–24.9</div>
              </div>
              <div class="stat-item">
                <div class="stat-label">Ideal Weight</div>
                <div class="stat-value stat-small" id="statIdeal">–</div>
              </div>
              <div class="stat-item">
                <div class="stat-label">BMI Prime</div>
                <div class="stat-value" id="statPrime">–</div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Health message -->
            <div class="health-message" id="healthMessage"></div>

            <!-- Weight to Lose/Gain -->
            <div class="weight-diff" id="weightDiff"></div>

            <!-- Calories CTA -->
            <div class="calories-cta" id="caloriesCta">
              <div class="cta-icon">
                <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 2a7 7 0 0 1 7 7c0 5-7 13-7 13S5 14 5 9a7 7 0 0 1 7-7z"/><circle cx="12" cy="9" r="2.5"/></svg>
              </div>
              <div class="cta-body">
                <p class="cta-title">Daily calories for your age?</p>
                <p class="cta-sub">Metabolic rates slow naturally as we age. Discover your age-adjusted calories.</p>
              </div>
              <a href="calories.html" class="cta-btn" id="ctaBtn">
                Calculate
                <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="9 18 15 12 9 6"/></svg>
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- BMI Classification Table -->
      <div class="card table-card scroll-reveal" style="--reveal-delay:0.05s" id="tableCard">
        <h3 class="section-title">Ideal BMI Thresholds by Age Group</h3>
        <p class="card-subtitle" style="margin-bottom:1rem">Note how the recommended weight ranges shift to support bone density and muscle preservation</p>
        <div class="table-wrapper">
          <table class="bmi-table" id="bmiTable">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Age Group</th>
                <th>Recommended BMI Range</th>
                <th>Health Target Focus</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Children & Teens (2–19)</strong></td>
                <td>5th to 85th Percentile</td>
                <td>Balanced growth velocity and healthy organ development.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Young & Middle Adults (20–64)</strong></td>
                <td>18.5 – 24.9</td>
                <td>Minimizing cardiovascular & metabolic disease risk factors.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Older Adults (65+)</strong></td>
                <td>22.0 – 29.0</td>
                <td>Preserving muscle mass, bone density, and surgical resilience.</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Demographic SEO Article -->
  <section class="landing-article">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="landing-article-inner scroll-reveal">
        <h2>The Complete Scientific Guide to BMI (Body Mass Index) by Age</h2>
        <p>In clinical medicine and nutritional science, the **Body Mass Index (BMI)** has served as the baseline diagnostic indicator for body fat levels for over a century. However, as scientific research has evolved, we have learned that flat BMI thresholds—such as classifying anyone with a score above 25 as overweight—do not represent health status equally across all ages. A child, a 30-year-old athlete, and a 75-year-old senior have completely different muscular frameworks, bone densities, and body fat requirements. This guide explains how age influences your BMI interpretation, the health recommendations for different stages of life, and why older adults benefit from maintaining a higher weight profile.</p>

        <h3>Childhood and Adolescence (Ages 2 to 19): The Growth Percentiles</h3>
        <p>During childhood and teenage years, body composition changes rapidly. A child's height increases in growth spurts, meaning a high BMI score at age 8 can be perfectly normal if they are about to experience a height growth spurt. Furthermore, boys and girls accumulate fat and muscle tissue at different velocities during puberty.</p>
        <p>Because of this constant change, **we cannot interpret children's BMI using standard adult thresholds**. Instead, pediatricians map a child's height and weight onto **CDC Growth Percentile Charts**. These charts compare the child's score to a national reference index of children of the exact same age and gender. A child between the **5th and 85th percentile** is classified as healthy weight. Percentiles above the 85th are classified as overweight, and those above the 95th indicate obesity.</p>

        <h3>Adulthood (Ages 20 to 64): The Standard WHO Thresholds</h3>
        <p>For young and middle-aged adults, the standard World Health Organization (WHO) classifications are highly reliable markers for metabolic health risks. During these decades, a BMI of **18.5 to 24.9** is considered the optimal healthy weight range. For example, a healthy weight for a 175 cm (5'9") adult in this age group is between 56.7 kg and 76.3 kg.</p>
        <p>Entering the overweight (25.0–29.9) or obese (30.0+) ranges in these years is directly linked to an increased risk of developing Type 2 diabetes, fatty liver disease, high blood pressure, and cardiovascular strain. Because metabolic rates are relatively stable compared to older years, adults in this group should aim to keep their BMI within the standard normal range through balanced nutrition and active lifestyles.</p>

        <h3>Older Adults (Ages 65 and Older): The Senior Survival Paradox</h3>
        <p>One of the most fascinating findings in geriatric medicine is the **"BMI Paradox"** (or obesity paradox) in seniors. Multiple large-scale epidemiological studies have demonstrated that for older adults, having a **slightly higher BMI is actually associated with better survival rates** and lower overall mortality. For seniors, the ideal BMI range is shifted upward to **22.0 – 29.0**.</p>
        <p>There are several crucial biological reasons for this shift:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Preventing Sarcopenia (Muscle Loss):</strong> Aging naturally causes muscle tissue depletion and weakness. Carrying a slightly higher body weight ensures a reserve of energy and encourages muscle use, protecting against frailty.</li>
          <li><strong>Bone Density Protection:</strong> A higher body weight puts stress on bones, which stimulates bone remodeling and helps prevent osteoporosis and fractures. If a senior falls, extra fat tissue provides physical cushioning, reducing hip fracture risks.</li>
          <li><strong>Resilience Against Chronic Illness:</strong> In the event of a severe medical incident (such as pneumonia, surgery, or stroke), seniors with higher energy reserves (slightly higher fat mass) have better survival rates than those who are lean or underweight.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>For seniors, being underweight (BMI under 22) is a far more immediate clinical danger than being slightly overweight.</p>

        <h3>Ideal Weight Targets by Life Stage Chart</h3>
        <p>The following chart summarizes the healthy weight and BMI targets recommended by medical associations across different age brackets:</p>
        
        <table class="ref-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Age Bracket</th>
              <th>Optimal BMI Range</th>
              <th>Primary Health Focus</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>Toddlers & Kids (2 - 9)</td>
              <td>5th - 85th Percentile</td>
              <td>Nutrient absorption, active motor play, skeletal growth.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Teens (10 - 19)</td>
              <td>5th - 85th Percentile</td>
              <td>Hormonal balance, muscle development, pubertal growth.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Young Adults (20 - 39)</td>
              <td>18.5 - 24.9</td>
              <td>Metabolic health, cardiovascular conditioning, weight maintenance.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Middle-Aged (40 - 64)</td>
              <td>18.5 - 24.9</td>
              <td>Preventing insulin resistance, monitoring visceral fat accumulation.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Seniors (65+)</td>
              <td>22.0 - 29.0</td>
              <td>Preserving skeletal muscle, maintaining bone density, preventing falls.</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <h3>How Metabolic Needs Shift With Age</h3>
        <p>As we get older, our **Basal Metabolic Rate (BMR)** slows down. This metabolic slowdown is not due to a broken metabolism; rather, it is because older bodies naturally carry less muscle mass (which burns more calories at rest) and because physical activity levels tend to decrease. To maintain a healthy BMI as you age, it is essential to focus on resistance training to preserve muscle tissue and adjust your daily calorie intake. Check your resting metabolic baseline with the <a href="/bmr.html">BMR Calculator</a>, calculate your total daily burn using the <a href="/tdee.html">TDEE Calculator</a>, or determine ideal body composition ratios using the <a href="/lean-body-mass.html">Lean Body Mass Calculator</a>.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Page Script -->
  <script src="/app.js" is:inline></script>
</Layout>
